@lauren_gilmour4 90's. Fortunate to get an audience with Edwin Morgan, pre exam time.
Even better was Iain Crichton Smith's visit.
Never fully appreciated at the time.

@MrMcEnaney @ryanyounie @sqanews If you don’t use the right symbols given in the equation sheet, the course support documents imply that you get 0 marks.
The general mark instructions say if the symbols you use are unambiguous, you should get full marks.
How many pupils will read it *that* way?
